#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:6
msgid "How to install and use plugins"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:8
msgid ""
"This section talks about installing and using third party plugins. For "
"writing your own plugins, please refer to :ref:`writing-plugins`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:11
msgid "Installing a third party plugin can be easily done with ``pip``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:13
msgid ""
"pip install pytest-NAME\n"
"pip uninstall pytest-NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:18
msgid ""
"If a plugin is installed, ``pytest`` automatically finds and integrates it, "
"there is no need to activate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:21
msgid "Here is a little annotated list for some popular plugins:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:23
msgid ""
":pypi:`pytest-django`: write tests for `django <https://docs.djangoproject."
"com/>`_ apps, using pytest integration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:26
msgid ""
":pypi:`pytest-twisted`: write tests for `twisted <https://twistedmatrix.com/"
">`_ apps, starting a reactor and processing deferreds from test functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:30
msgid ""
":pypi:`pytest-cov`: coverage reporting, compatible with distributed testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:33
msgid ""
":pypi:`pytest-xdist`: to distribute tests to CPUs and remote hosts, to run "
"in boxed mode which allows to survive segmentation faults, to run in "
"looponfailing mode, automatically re-running failing tests on file changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:39
msgid ""
":pypi:`pytest-instafail`: to report failures while the test run is happening."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:42
msgid ":pypi:`pytest-bdd`: to write tests using behaviour-driven testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:45
msgid ""
":pypi:`pytest-timeout`: to timeout tests based on function marks or global "
"definitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:48
msgid ""
":pypi:`pytest-pep8`: a ``--pep8`` option to enable PEP8 compliance checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:51
msgid ":pypi:`pytest-flakes`: check source code with pyflakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:54
msgid ""
":pypi:`allure-pytest`: report test results via `allure-framework <https://"
"github.com/allure-framework/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:57
msgid ""
"To see a complete list of all plugins with their latest testing status "
"against different pytest and Python versions, please visit :ref:`plugin-"
"list`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:61
msgid ""
"You may also discover more plugins through a `pytest- pypi.org search`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:69
msgid "Requiring/Loading plugins in a test module or conftest file"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:71
msgid ""
"You can require plugins in a test module or a conftest file using :globalvar:"
"`pytest_plugins`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:73
msgid "pytest_plugins = (\"myapp.testsupport.myplugin\",)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:77
msgid ""
"When the test module or conftest plugin is loaded the specified plugins will "
"be loaded as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:82
msgid ""
"Requiring plugins using a ``pytest_plugins`` variable in non-root ``conftest."
"py`` files is deprecated. See :ref:`full explanation <requiring plugins in "
"non-root conftests>` in the Writing plugins section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:88
msgid ""
"The name ``pytest_plugins`` is reserved and should not be used as a name for "
"a custom plugin module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:95
msgid "Finding out which plugins are active"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:97
msgid ""
"If you want to find out which plugins are active in your environment you can "
"type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:100
msgid "pytest --trace-config"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:104
msgid ""
"and will get an extended test header which shows activated plugins and their "
"names. It will also print local plugins aka :ref:`conftest.py <conftest.py "
"plugins>` files when they are loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:111
msgid "Deactivating / unregistering a plugin by name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:113
msgid "You can prevent plugins from loading or unregister them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:115
msgid "pytest -p no:NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:119
msgid ""
"This means that any subsequent try to activate/load the named plugin will "
"not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:122
msgid ""
"If you want to unconditionally disable a plugin for a project, you can add "
"this option to your ``pytest.ini`` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:125
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = -p no:NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:130
msgid ""
"Alternatively to disable it only in certain environments (for example in a "
"CI server), you can set ``PYTEST_ADDOPTS`` environment variable to ``-p no:"
"name``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:134
msgid "See :ref:`findpluginname` for how to obtain the name of a plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:139
msgid "Disabling plugins from autoloading"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:141
msgid ""
"If you want to disable plugins from loading automatically, instead of "
"requiring you to manually specify each plugin with ``-p`` or :envvar:"
"`PYTEST_PLUGINS`, you can use ``--disable-plugin-autoload`` or :envvar:"
"`PYTEST_DISABLE_PLUGIN_AUTOLOAD`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:144
msgid ""
"export PYTEST_DISABLE_PLUGIN_AUTOLOAD=1\n"
"export PYTEST_PLUGINS=NAME,NAME2\n"
"pytest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:150
msgid "pytest --disable-plugin-autoload -p NAME,NAME2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:154
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts =\n"
"        --disable-plugin-autoload\n"
"        -p NAME\n"
"        -p NAME2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/plugins.rst:164
msgid "The ``--disable-plugin-autoload`` command-line flag."
msgstr ""
